revision.text:
{{Infobox Newspaper | name = Alianza Metropolitan | caption = | type = Weekly newspaper | format =[[Broadsheet]] | owners = Rossana Drumond | editor = Gerardo Fernandez | circulation = 40,000 | headquarters =300 S. First Street, Suite 207, [[San Jose, CA]] 95113 [[United States]] | website =www.alianzanews.com |ceased publication= |foundation={{Start date|1986}} |oclc=34427239}}
'''Alianza Metropolitan''' is a bi-weekly bilingual, English and Spanish, newspaper that serves the Hispanic community in the greater metropolitan area of [[San Jose, California]]. The paper was founded in 1986<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn96061010/|title=Alianza metropolitan news. [volume]|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> and is currently 100% Hispanic owned,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.willowglen.org/business-alianza-metropolitan-news-1864|title=ABOUT ALIANZA METROPOLITAN NEWS|last=|first=|date=|website=WILLOW GLENarchive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=20 October 2018}}</ref> by Rossana Drumond and previously by George Villalobos. The paper is edited by Gerardo Fernandez. The website of the newspaper is in Spanish. The paper's estimated circulation totals 40,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mondotimes.com/1/world/us/5/317/25326|title=Alianza Metropolitan newspaper - MondoTimes.com|website=www.mondotimes.com|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref>
==History==
Alianza Metropolitan was founded in 1986 by George Villalobos.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlianzaNews|title=Alianza News (@AlianzaNews) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
In 1996, San Jose Mercury News, owned by media conglomerate [[Knight Ridder|Knight Ridder,]] established ''Nuevo Mundo'' and its Spanish language weekly subsidiary to compete directly with the three local Hispanic-owned papers: ''La Ofreta'', ''El Observador'', and ''Alianza''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metroactive.com/papers/metro/05.29.97/spanish-press-9722.html|title=Metroactive News & Issues {{!}} Hispanic Newspapers|website=www.metroactive.com|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> Within months of its launch, Nuevo Mundo began drawing readership and advertising away from the three papers, causing financial troubles for the local papers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metroactive.com/papers/metro/05.29.97/spanish-press-9722.html|title=Metroactive News & Issues {{!}} Hispanic Newspapers|website=www.metroactive.com|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref> In 2005 Mercury News shut down its foreign language subsidiaries including ''Nuevo Mundo.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://juantornoe.blogs.com/hispanictrending/2005/10/san_jose_mercur.html|title=HispanicTrending: San Jose Mercury News unloads foreign language newspapers|website=juantornoe.blogs.com|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref>
Current publisher Rossana Drumond is Region VI Chair for the National Association of Hispanic Publications.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://nahp.org/about-nahp/leadership/|title=Leadership|last=|first=|date=|website=National Association of Hispanic Publications|access-date=20 October 2018}}</ref> In 2017, Drumond was voted "Publisher of the Year" by the NAHP.<ref name=":1" />
