{{nofootnotes|date=February 2010}}
'''Big Blue Books''' are a series of small staple-bound books published from 1925 to 1950 by the Haldeman-Julius Publishing Company of [[Girard, Kansas]] (1919–1978), larger than the [[Little Blue Book]]s.  The series included both reprints and first publications, the latter including ''An Outline of Intellectual Rubbish'' by [[Bertrand Russell]].

