s-brings-superman-vs-muhammad-ali-concept-for-a-rematch-with-harley-quinn.html NEAL ADAMS Brings SUPERMAN vs. MUHAMMAD ALI Concept For A Rematch... With HARLEY QUINN] By Vaneta Rogers, Newsarama, 1 Jul 2016</ref>|group=note|name=alifight}} 2016) *''[[House of Mystery]]'', vol. 1, #178-179, 186, 228 (1969–75) *''House of Mystery'', vol. 2, #13 (2009) *''Justice for All includes Children'' #1-2, 6-7 (public service pages, 1976) *''[[Justice League|Justice League of America]]'' #94 (four pages, 1971) *''The Kamandi Challenge'' #2 (2017) *''[[Our Army at War]]'' #182-183, 186, 240 (1967–72) *''[[Phantom Stranger]]'', vol. 2, #4 (1969) *''[[Spectre (comics)|Spectre]]'' #2-5 (1968) *''[[Star Spangled War Stories]]'' #134, 144 (1967–69) *''[[Strange Adventures]]'' ([[Deadman (DC Comics)|Deadman]]) #206-211, 214 (art); #212-213, 215-216 (writer/art) (1967–69) *''[[Superman (comic book)|Superman]]'' ("Private Life of [[Clark Kent]]") #254 (1972) *''[[Superman]]: The Coming of the Supermen'', miniseries, #1-6 (writer/art) (2016) *''[[Teen Titans]]'' #20-22 (1969) *''[[Weird Western Tales]]'' ([[El Diablo (comics)|El Diablo]]) #12-13, 15 (1972) *''[[The Witching Hour (DC Comics)|Witching Hour]]'' #8 (1970) *''[[World's Finest Comics]]'' (Superman/Batman) #175-176 (1968) {{div col end}}
